==English==
===Etymology===
From Latinised {{Gr.}} [[collectus]], from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[συλλεκτός]]''' (''syllectos'') "gathered or brought together", from '''[[συλλέγω]]''' (''syllego'') "bring together, collect, gather, compile", from prefix '''[[συλ-]]''' (''syl-'') "with, togther, along with, accompanied by, in, at the same time" + '''[[λέγω]]''' (''lego'') "to gather, pick up, to choose for oneself, pick out, to count."

===Noun===
#A set of [[item]]s or [[object]]s [[procure]]d by an individual
#Multiple related objects associated as a [[group]]
